{{- define "code-planner-tools" -}}

CODE PLANNER TOOLS:
- liza submit-for-review — Submit code plan for review
  liza submit-for-review {{.TaskID}} <SHA> --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
  Submission requires a new worktree commit for this task: stage the intended files, create the submission commit, confirm `git -C {{.Worktree}} status --short` is clean, then get the SHA with `git -C {{.Worktree}} rev-parse HEAD`. Do NOT submit the pre-change HEAD.
{{template "await-verdict-loop" .}}
- liza write-checkpoint — Write pre-execution checkpoint (REQUIRED before submission)
  liza write-checkpoint {{.TaskID}} --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --intent "<what>" --validation-plan "<how to verify>" --files-to-modify "<file1>" --json
- liza set-task-output — Persist structured task definitions for downstream task creation
  liza set-task-output {{.TaskID}} --output {{.Worktree}}/specs/plans/{{.GoalSlug}}/TIMESTAMP-{{.TaskID}}-output.json --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
  Use the same TIMESTAMP as the plan file from Implementation Phase step 2.
  Create that JSON file next to the plan file with a file-writing tool, not a Bash heredoc (heredoc with JSON triggers a shell safety block).
  Do NOT write task-output JSON under .liza/agent-outputs/; that directory is runtime state, not a committed plan artifact location.
  JSON file contains: [
    {"desc": "...", "done_when": "...", "scope": "...", "spec_ref": "...", "plan_ref": "...", "depends_on": ["0", "2"]}
  ]
  depends_on: optional array of sibling index strings. "0" means "depends on output[0]".
  Indices are resolved to child task IDs at transition time.
- liza handoff — Context near exhaustion (~90%)
  liza handoff {{.TaskID}} "<what is done>" "<exact next step>" --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
- liza mark-blocked — Cannot proceed
  liza mark-blocked {{.TaskID}} --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --reason "<what is blocking>" --questions "<q1>" --questions "<q2>" --json
  If a command failure is the blocker, `--reason` MUST include the exact failing command and stderr/error text. Do NOT infer root cause without a captured failure.
{{- end -}}
